---
// 4. The bet — the thesis. States the actual claim the site is built from.
// Without this section the page is a thoughtful list of questions; with it,
// it's a point of view. This is the missing beat the homepage was lacking.
---

<section class="relative">
  <div class="container-page py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-[1fr_2fr] md:gap-16">
      <p class="font-mono text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-bone-300">
        The bet
      </p>
      <div>
        <p
          class="max-w-[58ch] text-[26px] leading-[1.22] tracking-tight text-bone-300 md:text-[36px] md:leading-[1.18]"
          style="text-wrap: balance;"
        >
          <span class="text-bone-0">
            Working well with AI is going to require a deeper understanding of
            problem-solving itself than we have right now.
          </span>
        </p>

        <p class="mt-10 max-w-[60ch] text-[16.5px] leading-[1.7] text-bone-300">
          Not solving as in computation — solving as in framing the question,
          recognizing what's structured and what isn't, knowing when an answer
          is the one you actually wanted. That isn't a footnote. It's the
          thing.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-6 max-w-[60ch] text-[16.5px] leading-[1.7] text-bone-300">
          <span class="text-bone-0">This site is the lab where I'm working it out.</span>
          A notebook to think out loud, tools to put the thinking to work, and
          a map of how the ideas connect.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
